# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# These are base image CVEs (Debian slim) that are not in our application code.
# They will be resolved when the base image publisher releases a patched version.

# perl-archive-tar: Path traversal via crafted tar files
# Affects perl-base in Debian slim; not exploitable in our container
# (we don't use perl or Archive::Tar)
CVE-2026-42496

# perl-Archive-Tar: Arbitrary file overwrite
# Same perl-base package, same reasoning
CVE-2026-42497

# perl: Heap buffer overflow when compiling regular expressions
# perl-base in Debian slim; not exploitable in our container
CVE-2026-8376

# perl: silently incorrect regular expression results
# perl-base in Debian slim; not exploitable in our container
CVE-2026-13221

# tar (node-tar): Denial of Service via crafted gzip bomb
# Bundled with npm in node:22-alpine base image; not exploitable in our Next.js container
CVE-2026-59873
